short_description: Situated on the vibrant Wanstead High Street, boasting views overlooking the immaculately kept communal gardens and across Wanstead, this luxurious apartment is within easy reach of both
full_description:
Tenure: Share of Freehold

Situated on the vibrant Wanstead High Street, boasting views overlooking the immaculately kept communal gardens and across Wanstead, this luxurious apartment is within easy reach of both Snaresbrook (0.1 miles) and Wanstead Central Line stations (0.4 miles). This prestigious gated development of purpose built apartments are renowned for their spacious accommodation and fantastic layouts as well as it's convenient location being within and easy reach of the popular shops, restaurants, coffee shops and everything else that Wanstead High Street has to offer.
The property is accessed via a secure entry phone system that leads you into an immaculate communal hallway, with the sixth floor being accessible by either stairs or lift. At 894 square foot, it is not only the size that is extremely impressive, but as you enter the hallway, the high quality finish really does create the wow factor. The large lounge/diner at the rear is the perfect place to unwind or entertain in and features large windows offering fantastic views, as a home cinema system, up lighting and new UPVC bi-folds leading out onto the balcony.

The master bedroom offers rare features such as air-conditioning, ceiling speakers and mood lighting, whilst the second double bedroom has the advantage of multi functioning fitted furniture with a large desk unit that converts effortlessly into a double bed. The stunning kitchen has everything you could possibly desire in a kitchen, including a huge American fridge/freezer, recessed domino-hobs, integrated Siemens oven and an additional microwave oven with warming drawers. All of which are surrounded with stylish bespoke walnut effect cabinets and solid granite work tops. The kitchen can be used solely as an area to prepare meals in as there is also a separate and well-designed utility room, housing the washing machine, highly efficient mega flow system and storage to house all of your essential but unsightly cleaning products.The epitome of high quality continues into the bathroom, where the bespoke fixtures include twin sinks with waterfall taps, designer Italian tiles, large walk-in rain shower, stand-alone tap less bath, recessed towel rail, top-lit recess feature storage, lots of under-sink storage and ceiling speakers.

This imposing double-fronted Victorian semi-detached house has been wonderfully cared for and updated by the current owner. The exterior is impeccably presented and internally the property has been reimagined with the emphasis placed on ensuring that there is a sense of light and space throughout. Extending to over four thousand square feet the property has two formal reception rooms with two further basement rooms and an impressive fully equipped kitchen/diner with doors leading to the large rear garden. short_description: This exceptional detached family home is situated in arguably Wanstead's most prestigious turning, backing onto Wanstead Golf Course with pleasing views of the greens and rolling hills.
full_description:
Tenure: Freehold

This exceptional detached family home is situated in arguably Wanstead's most prestigious turning, backing onto Wanstead Golf Course with pleasing views of the greens and rolling hills. This stunning architecturally designed home has all the qualities that certainly set it apart from your average home. It has been designed with family life in mind. The layout is beautiful, practical and functional, ideal for today's modern living.

Upon entering you are greeted with a spacious entrance hall. The large open plan kitchen/diner has a 'wow'! factor and is the hub of the home. Bifold doors open the full length of the rear of the property, also adding an abundance of light to this huge area, merging the generous patio with the open plan kitchen/diner and living space overlooking the landscaped garden, making the whole area ideal for grand social events such as birthdays etc. Two further receptions makes it easy for those who work from home to have a study, great for the children to do their homework away from the distractions of the main home. Four double bedrooms have all unique design features and allow guests to stay in comfort. The master bedroom has a walk in wardrobe and boutique style en suite, matching the large family bathroom, ideal to relax, indulge and pamper yourself.

Although situated within a quiet peaceful location, you will be surprised how very conveniently it is for the High Street with excellent restaurants, bars and Wanstead Central Line station.

What the Owner says:


We get the best of both worlds with this house. A countryside feel with open expansive views across the golf course and yet still a short walk from the High Street and tube.

We love the proximity to the tennis and cricket clubs as well as the stunning Wanstead Park which is a constant feature of our weekends.

We have great neighbours and a community spirit. We have built up a strong network of close friends during our time here. We have loved hosting parties in the amazing garden in the summer and in the large open plan entertaining space in winter.

short_description: The property has full planning approval to create a six bedroom, detached home with six shower rooms/bathrooms, two walk in wardrobes, home cinema and underground car parking facilities..
full_description:
Tenure: Freehold

The property has full planning approval to create a six bedroom, detached home with six shower rooms/bathrooms, two walk in wardrobes, home cinema and underground car parking facilities with gym, spa, work room and large entertainment area. Such a rare opportunity is rarely available and will likely not be seen again as St Mary's Avenue is Wanstead's most desirable and sought after road. Tree-lined and edged with large, impressive homes situated on large plots, residents are well connected with Epping Forest, Wanstead High Street and Wanstead station all within close proximity. Currently the plot is occupied by a four bedroom detached bungalow in need of cosmetic updating, with two bathrooms, two separate toilets, kitchen/diner with separate utility room, large lounge and integral garage. The garden is a fantastic size and there is a deep drive with off road parking to the front for several vehicles. 

Planning permission has been fully approved and plans drawn up for the current dwelling to be demolished in favour of an impressive six bedroom, four storey home, with the lower storey being set beneath ground level. If the buyer were to carry out the approved plans they would be able to create a huge home in an idyllic location. Upon entering the home you would be presented with an impressive entrance hall which would lead to a grand formal reception, home cinema room, a shower room and store area and huge open plan living area to the rear boasting a study space, lounge, kitchen/diner and large walk-in pantry. The large bi-fold door leading from the living area would allow you to access a raised paved patio area with plenty of entertainment and seating space and a view of the sunken courtyard below.

To the first floor there would be three spacious double bedrooms, all with en-suite facilities, and a large store cupboard leading off of the landing area. Both the master suite and bedroom two to this floor would have space to accommodate a seating area in the main bedroom and enjoy the benefit of a generous walk-in-wardrobe. To the third floor the remaining three bedrooms and office would be found, with one bedroom benefitting from an en-suite and the remaining two bedrooms sharing a large bathroom with separate bath and shower. 

Finally, the home has planning for an exceptional basement area, allowing the property to stand apart from those generally found in the area. A car lift would provide the ability to securely store two cars, whist the remaining space would be occupied by a gym, spa area, W.C, storage and plant area and large entertaining space and bar area that would overlook and enjoy access to a sunken courtyard.

short_description: This 1700sq ft four bedroom, semi-detached, Victorian-period family home sits proudly on Addison Road, Wanstead- 0.2 miles from Wanstead Station and High Street.
full_description:
Tenure: Freehold

This 1700sq ft four bedroom, semi-detached, Victorian-period family home sits proudly on Addison Road, Wanstead- 0.2 miles from Wanstead Station and High Street. 

Providing new owners with the opportunity to live on one of Wanstead's most sought after locations, this property has been maintained by the current owners and the majority of the period-features have been retained.

To the front of the property are the well-presented drive way and imposing bay windows. As you enter you will notice the generous hall way which is perfectly complimented by the high ceilings. This is a recurring theme throughout.

The front reception room is considerable and boasts a wealth of original features such as original coving, cornicing and ceiling rose.

Towards the rear of the property sits the fully-fitted kitchen with breakfast bar and storage units and leads through to the dining room and finally through to the back reception room and study with WC.

The garden has been fully landscaped and well maintained by the current owners.

To the first floor are four bedrooms, family bathroom and separate WC. The master bedroom has built in wardrobes and feature bay window. The property provides a spacious living arrangement and the opportunity to convert the loft space into further bedrooms and bathroom- STPP.

full_description:
Tenure: Freehold

This attractive semi detached family home can be found within the popular Warren Estate and only a short stroll to Wanstead High Street with its array of supermarkets, excellent bars, restaurants and Central Line station.

The location of the property is further complemented by having Wanstead Golf Course and Wanstead Park on its doorstep!

This well presented period home has an abundance of charm and character with many original features. The current owner has maintained the property to a very high standard giving this home a cosy feel throughout. Internal viewings are highly recommended.

For those families with schools in mind, there are a number of private and high achieving public schools to choose from, including Forest, Our Lady of Lourdes and Wanstead Church School.

There are also many recreational facilities to include tennis, golf, cricket, football and horse riding stables all on your doorstep for the whole families' pleasure.

Commuters are well served by Wanstead Central Line station just a short walk away with fast direct access to the City, Docklands and the West End.

What the Owner says:


This is a great family home in a location that is perfect for young families as there is so much for children to do around here.

There is a real sense of community here, we have wonderful neighbours.

We have always liked the feeling that you are in a rural setting although we are in London. Not many other areas in London can say they are surrounded by forests and heaths.

It is an absolute delight to live so close to Wanstead Park especially in the summer. It's like a hidden oasis.

short_description: A substantial, elegantly appointed four bedroom semi detached, in our ever popular Warren Estate neighborhood of broad sweeping avenues surrounded by natural green spaces.
full_description:
A substantial, elegantly appointed four bedroom semi detached, in our ever popular Warren Estate neighborhood of broad sweeping avenues surrounded by natural green spaces. With Wanstead High Street, the heart of this increasingly popular East London village, less than a half mile on foot.

As generous as the property is, there's scope for further development with the loft space so far unconverted. Subject to the usual permissions you could, as your neighbours have, add a whole extra storey to this already grand property, making this an uncommonly good investment.

IF YOU LIVED HERE...

You'll be stretching out in almost 1500 square feet of impeccably finished living space, with the front reception alone coming in at 220 square feet, all bright and brimming with vintage touches from the ceiling rose and cornicing overhead to the original floorboards underfoot. Your separate dining room is still more spacious, a hair under 300 square feet artfully separated by a bespoke fretwork arch. 

Double patio doors lead out into the sixty foot, south facing rear garden. An elegantly landscaped affair, it begins with a generous patio - ideal for barbecues and al fresco dining of all kinds â before descending to an immaculate length of lawn flanked by paths, raised beds and timber fencing. There's a beautiful central bed with a rose arch before it ends in a second patio with a pair of sheds. An amazing space.

Back inside and the ground floor is completed by a spare WC and laundry room, plus the kitchen, decked out in a smart timber suite. Head upstairs (past some gorgeous vintage stained glass) and you have a large landing with plenty of fitted storage. The capacious master bedroom comes in at over 200 square feet, with more original timber underfoot. Bedrooms two and three are both solid doubles of 100 and 130 square feet respectively, both with leafy garden views.

Bedroom four is a generous single of 90 square feet, ideal for a child, home office or dressing room while, finally, the family bathroom is an elegant, understated affair in pale grey, with a tub and separate shower cubicle. Outside, Wanstead tube station is less than a half mile on foot and will whisk you directly into Liverpool Street in just eighteen minutes via the Central Line.

Once a royal hunting ground and the favoured country retreat of Henry VIII, Wanstead's rural past is still apparent in its multitude of open green spaces, from Epping Forest to Wanstead Flats. George Green and Christ Church Green flank the bustling High Street, a rich collection of independent shops, supermarkets and excellent bars, restaurants and gastropubs. Try the Manor House, a wonderfully stylish establishment that does a great Sunday Roast.

WHAT ELSE?

- Local schools are excellent, you have eight primary/secondaries within a one mile radius, four rated 'Good' by Ofsted and four deemed 'Outstanding'.
- You have off street parking for two cars, and drivers can be on the North Circular in less than five minutes.
- Wanstead High Street is great, but be sure to check out Nightingale Lane just a little further on, it's home to some lovely traditional pubs from The Duke, to The Lane to The Nightingale On The Green.

A WORD FROM THE OWNER....

"After almost twenty eight years in our lovely home we now feel that it is time that our home welcomed a new family. We are just around the corner from Wanstead High School which two of our boys attended and enjoyed. When we moved in, all four of our boys were still at home. They have all all since fled the nest and we feel that our home is ready to welcome a new family. My husband is a very keen gardener and we had lorry loads of topsoil delivered to allow him to grow our own vegetables which the south facing garden lends itself to. We have wonderful neighbours and we shall miss them but take away fond memories of our time here. It has been a great family home!"

short_description: Proudly positioned on a corner plot with views over the Wanstead Flats and close to Bushwood and Wanstead Park, this stunning home makes a striking first impression, with the imposing
full_description:
Tenure: Freehold

Proudly positioned on a corner plot with views over the Wanstead Flats and close to Bushwood and Wanstead Park, this stunning home makes a striking first impression, with the imposing turret frontage, wrap around front garden and beautiful Edwardian features. Set on the tree lined Richmond Way, this substantial home offers beautifully maintained period features alongside contemporary living and layout. Stepping inside the ornate hallway you will discover a large lounge, dining room and an airy kitchen, which enjoys views over the garden. The spacious lounge provides a beautiful place to relax in thanks to the tasteful decor and the room's focal points, such as the feature fireplace, large bay window and characterful detailing of the cornicing and skirting boards. The dining room is equally as impressive with double aspect views over the garden and a kitchen, which has plenty of storage and work surface space. With these two rooms connecting seamlessly, it creates a fantastic entertaining space. Although these three rooms create a large, 'open plan' sense of living, there is also the addition of a separate reception room that features the stunning turret and bay window overlooking Wanstead flats and creates a peaceful area to escape to and could be used as a formal dining room or second TV room if desired. There is also a large handy cellar, which is accessible from the hallway and provides ideal storage space. To the first floor there is a modern family bathroom and four bedrooms, with the stunning master bedroom enjoying a large bay window and a great deal of space.

Externally, the advantage of the corner position allows the rear garden to wrap around the house and has been thoughtfully designed to create three distinct areas: a large raised decked area, perfect for hosting BBQ's or summer parties, a spacious artificial grassed area, which is perfect for the children to play on and a beautiful oasis of mature shrubs and plants, providing the perfect shady retreat. The icing on the cake with this home is the large double garage at the rear of the garden that has been converted to provide a large useable space with electricity, which depending on your needs could be used as a play room, office, gym, or a summer house.

To the first floor there is a family bathroom and four bedrooms, three of which are generous doubles with the fourth a good office/single bedroom or nursery. To the rear there is a large, low maintenance garden which is laid to lawn and patio but has plenty of potential for a keen gardener.

full_description:

Without a doubt one of the most uniquely positioned homes in Wanstead today, this semi-detached Georgian cottage is a rare survivor from the time of Wanstead House - then termed the 'English Versailles'. Wanstead's thriving High Street boasts a large number of independent cafÃ©'s, bar's restaurants and shops as well as a large number of fantastic schools and transport links. Set on the High Street but separated by a large garden towards the front, this home has the advantage of having everything Wanstead has to offer on your doorstep and is just a short walk from both Snaresbrook (500 feet) and Wanstead Central Line Station (0.4 miles).

Set back to rear of the plot, this cottage and its approach are the epitome of quintessential English charm - from the pristine green lawn encased by black wrought iron railings, to the sash windows, wooden shutters and weather-boarded exterior. Stepping inside, you immediately enter the dining room with a central fire place and large storage cupboard, which is perfect for shoes and coats or utility items. Leading from the dining room you pass a handy downstairs W.C as you enter into a large, bright contemporary kitchen/breakfast room, which benefits from great deal of natural light thanks to the stunning apex skylight and floor-to-ceiling bi-folding doors. There is a cosy, separate lounge with a central fireplace and a third reception room, which could be used as a study, office or third bedroom depending on your needs. Moving upstairs, the landing provides access to a modern bathroom and two double bedrooms; both enjoying a central fireplace and the master enjoying an en-suite shower room. Both bedrooms have large sash windows making the upstairs feel bright and airy. The property further benefits from secure bike and bin storage towards the front.

Located in central Wanstead, only 0.3 miles from Wanstead High Street with its popular array of bars, restaurants, and shops, such as the renowned Ginger Pig and Gail's Bakery you are close to everything Wanstead has to offer. In addition to this you are 0.4 miles to Snaresbrook and 0.3miles to Wanstead Central Line stations, both of which offer quick and easy access to central London, making it ideal for city commuters. The icing on the cake with this location is the close proximity to the excellent Roman Catholic and Church of England junior schools and within a mile of several good non-denominational schools. For families, there are also cricket, bowls and tennis clubs and a leisure center which is about to benefit from a new swimming pool catering for the local community. To top all of this, you are a stone's throw away from the open spaces of the iconic Christ Church Green and Wanstead Park. Stepping inside, there are two large connecting reception rooms featuring a large bay window to the front, flooding the room with natural light, and direct access to the rear garden from the lounge. To the rear of the property there is a separate dining room that features an attractive side bay and a well-proportioned newly fitted kitchen that has a good deal of storage and floor space. 

There is also a conservatory leading from the kitchen, which presents a fantastic opportunity for the next buyer to create a fabulous kitchen/diner/utility room by connecting the rear rooms or by further extending the kitchen (STPC). To the first floor there are three good sized double bedrooms and a bathroom with separate toilet, which is accessed via a charming split level landing. There is further potential to extend into the loft creating a further bedroom with en-suite (STPC). The charming, idyllic, south facing 'English Country Garden' is a good size and offers a colourful, low maintenance mix of lawn, shrubs and roses. There is further, handy off road parking to the front.
